slides.title: Sloane
slides.body: Sloane has a sleek, confident vibe that works perfectly as a gender-neutral baby name. It's got that modern, upscale ring to it without being too out there. Sloane literally means “raider” or “warrior,” so it has roots in strength and independence—how cool is that? It's short, easy to spell, and sounds elegant whether paired with a middle name or standing on its own. If you're into unique unisex names with edge, Sloane might be your perfect pick.

cards.title: India’s home fortress falls: Ex-India cricketer Dinesh Karthik says 'aura has disappeared’ after SA whitewash
cards.abstract: South Africa's dominant 2-0 Test series victory over India has sparked concerns about the team's Test cricket form. Former player Dinesh Karthik highlighted a concerning decline, citing bowlers being outplayed, batting struggles, and inconsistent selection. He questioned the frequent changes at the crucial No. 3 position, emphasizing the need for stability to regain past glory.

cards.abstract: The shares of Paytm-parent One 97 Communications jumped around 2 percent in the early trading hours of November 27 after the company announced that its subsidiary has received Reserve Bank of India's (RBI) final approval for Payment Aggregator license.
